direct state management preserves destination using sessionStorage with priority resolution"}, "clearVisualFeedback": {"status": "pass", "requirement": "Clear visual feedback when session expires", "verification": "SessionExpiredModal displays countdown, destination, and actionable button"}, "sessionDuration24Hours": {"status": "pass", "requirement": "Session remains valid for 24 hours of inactivity", "verification": "Backend JWT configuration uses 24h expiration with proper ConfigService integration and fallback defaults"}, "properAuthStateClearing": {"status": "pass", "requirement": "Auth state is properly cleared on logout and timeout", "verification": "clearAuthState() removes all tokens and broadcasts to other tabs (lines 152-159)"}, "immediateRedirectOnExpiration": {"status": "pass", "requirement": "User is immediately redirected to login on session expiration", "verification": "Session expiration event system triggers immediate redirect via AuthContext (lines 106-125)"}}, "criticalRequirements": {"unifiedHttpClient": {"status": "pass", "findings": ["✅ PASS: Created unified ApiClient class in api.client.ts (line 18-196)", "✅ PASS: Implements request interceptor to add auth tokens (lines 39-50)", "✅ PASS: Implements response interceptor for 401 handling (lines 53-120)", "✅ PASS: Request queueing system implemented correctly (lines 21-24, 64-77)", "✅ PASS: Refresh lock mechanism prevents concurrent refreshes (line 20, 64, 80, 114)", "✅ PASS: Queue processing after successful refresh (lines 92-93)", "✅ PASS: Queue rejection on refresh failure (lines 102-103)", "✅ PASS: Automatic retry of original request after token refresh (line 96)", "✅ PASS: Exported as singleton instance: apiClient (line 198)"], "severity": "n/a", "compliance": 100, "requirement": "Implement unified HTTP client with automatic token refresh and request queueing to replace fragmented axios instances", "recommendation": "Excellent implementation. Consider documenting the request queuing mechanism in code comments for future maintainers."}, "backendJwtConfiguration": {"status": "partial_pass", "findings": ["✅ PASS: auth.service.ts correctly implements configurable JWT expiration via ConfigService", "✅ PASS: auth.module.ts JwtModule.registerAsync uses configurable expiration (line 22: expiresIn: config.get('JWT_EXPIRES_IN', '24h'))", "✅ PASS: Default fallback values are correct ('24h' and '30d')", "⚠️  DEVIATION: .env file shows JWT_EXPIRES_IN='15m' instead of '24h' (line 15)", "⚠️  DEVIATION: .env file shows JWT_REFRESH_EXPIRES_IN='7d' instead of '30d' (line 17)"], "severity": "low", "compliance": 85, "requirement": "Configure JWT access token expiration to 24 hours and refresh token to 30 days", "recommendation": "Update .env file to match architectural specifications. The code implementation is correct with proper defaults, but production configuration should be explicit."}, "multiTabSynchronization": {"status": "pass", "findings": ["✅ PASS: BroadcastChannel 'auth_channel' created in AuthContext (line 40)", "✅ PASS: Message handlers for TOKEN_UPDATED, LOGOUT, and LOGIN events (lines 43-59)", "✅ PASS: Fallback to storage events when BroadcastChannel not supported (lines 60-96)", "✅ PASS: Token update broadcast in api.client.ts (lines 161-178)", "✅ PASS: Logout broadcast in api.client.ts (lines 180-191)", "✅ PASS: Login broadcast in AuthContext (lines 132-139)", "✅ PASS: Proper cleanup of BroadcastChannel on unmount (lines 98-102)", "✅ PASS: Cross-tab auth state synchronization verified in tests"], "severity": "n/a", "compliance": 100, "requirement": "Implement multi-tab synchronization using BroadcastChannel API with localStorage fallback", "recommendation": "Implementation follows architectural specifications perfectly."}, "redirectStateManagement": {"status": "pass", "findings": ["✅ PASS: redirectPath state variable in AuthContext (line 22)", "✅ PASS: Session expiration handler saves redirect path (lines 106-125)", "✅ PASS: Uses sessionStorage.setItem('r