ac0dfdb4-3c13-4083-9d99-9ef52c59837b	345a29ee-d6ab-477d-8079-c5dda0844d77	64a163e5-e3cb-43cd-bc3c-410dbb1848e0	ST-1	bug	Database Disaster Recovery & Mandatory Backup Implementation	## Incident Summary\n\nOn 2025-11-15, a critical database disaster occurred during Docker container rebuild that resulted in complete loss of production data.\n\n### Root Cause\nDocker Compose volume naming mismatch:\n- Old volume: `aistudio_postgres-data` (hyphen) - 49.5MB, created Nov 8\n- New volume: `aistudio_postgres_data` (underscore) - created during rebuild\n\nWhen containers were rebuilt, Docker created a new empty volume instead of using the existing production data volume.\n\n### Impact\n- **Lost Data**: 1 project, 20+ stories, use cases, connected commits\n- **Database State**: System catalog corruption in old volume (pg_authid table missing)\n- **Recovery Attempts**: Multiple approaches failed including pg_filedump, single-user mode, trust authentication, data file transplantation\n\n### Recovery Actions Taken\n1. ✅ Identified volume mismatch issue\n2. ✅ Located old volume with 49.5MB data\n3. ❌ Standard PostgreSQL recovery failed due to catalog corruption\n4. ✅ Application restored with empty database\n5. ✅ New admin user created (admin@aistudio.local)\n6. ✅ **CRITICAL FIX**: Added mandatory database backup requirement to Software Architect component instructions\n\n### Prevention Measures Implemented\n**Software Architect Component** now includes:\n- Mandatory pg_dump before ANY schema modifications\n- Backup verification steps\n- Backup location documentation\n- Recovery plan requirement\n\n**Coordinator Instructions** updated with:\n- Database backup requirement warning\n- Backup verification checklist\n- Recovery procedures\n\n### Files Involved\n- `/opt/stack/AIStudio/docker-compose.prod.yml` - Volume definition issue\n- `/opt/stack/AIStudio/backend/Dockerfile.prod` - Production build\n- `/opt/stack/AIStudio/backend/prisma/schema.prisma` - Schema changes from ST-27\n- Docker volumes: `aistudio_postgres-data` vs `aistudio_postgres_data`\n\n### Lessons Learned\n1. ALWAYS backup database before schema migrations\n2. Verify Docker volume names match existing volumes\n3. Test database connectivity after container rebuilds\n4. Implement automated backup strategy	planning	10	9	8	\N	\N	5269e325-16c7-4400-85a8-215aee7a2074	2025-11-17 10:04:49.893	2025-11-17 10:04:49.893	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	0	\N	\N	\N	0
423cdc7e-ffae-4d05-9c2f-ec30f321a323	345a29ee-d6ab-477d-8079-c5dda0844d77	9ecdbb94-28b7-4358-94f0-a7280f466227	ST-19	feature	Implement reliable data loading mechanism for workflow subagents	## Problem Statement\n\nCurrently, when workflow components spawn subagents (e.g., Architect, Designer, BA), there's no guaranteed mechanism to ensure these agents receive all necessary contextual data from the database. For instance:\n\n- When Architect agent is spawned, it should reliably receive UX designs, test cases, and exploration fields\n- When Designer agent runs, it needs access to architect analysis and requirements\n- When BA agent executes, it requires complete story context and related use cases\n\nThe current implementation lacks a rock-solid data loading pattern that guarantees data availability for subagents.\n\n## Requirements\n\n1. **Design a robust data fetching pattern** that components can use before spawning subagents\n2. **Create helper functions/utilities** for loading complete story context including:\n   - Story details (title, description, status, complexity)\n   - Related fields (contextExploration, architectAnalysis, baAnalysis, designerAnalysis, uxDesigns)\n   - Linked use cases with their details\n   - Test cases\n   - Related files and code metrics\n   - Epic context if applicable\n3. **Implement data validation** to verify all expected data is present before agent spawn\n4. **Add clear error handling** when required data is missing\n5. **Document the pattern** so all component developers know how to properly load data for their agents\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] Data loading utilities are implemented and tested\n- [ ] All workflow components use the standardized data loading pattern\n- [ ] Subagents receive complete, validated context data every time\n- [ ] Clear error messages when data is missing or incomplete\n- [ ] Documentation exists for the data loading pattern\n- [ ] Integration tests verify data reliability across different workflow scenarios\n\n## Technical Notes\n\nConsider implementing:\n- A `StoryContextLoader` class or utility module\n- Typed interfaces for complete story context\n- Validation schemas to ensure data completeness\n- Caching mechanism to avoid redundant database queries within same workflow run\n- Logging/telemetry to track data loading success/failures	planning	9	\N	7	\N	\N	5269e325-16c7-4400-85a8-215aee7a2074	2025-11-18 14:13:22.753	2025-11-18 14:13:22.753	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	0	\N	\N	\N	0
c050178c-44c6-4fa1-aa36-05e5a93623d6	345a29ee-d6ab-477d-8079-c5dda0844d77	3e6294d7-e8ef-4005-a670-64db9bbdf3c0	ST-20	feature	Create centralized story context loader utility	## Objective\nCreate a centralized utility function that loads complete story context in a single database query, providing a standardized way for workflows to retrieve all necessary data.\n\n## Requirements\n\n1. **Add TypeScript Interfaces** (`backend/src/mcp/utils.ts`):\n   - `StoryFullContext` interface containing:\n     - `story`: All story fields (id, key, title, description, status, type, complexities, analysis fields)\n     - `project`: Project details (id, name, repositoryUrl, localPath)\n     - `epic`: Epic details (id, key, title, description) or null\n     - `useCases`: Array of use cases with latest versions\n     - `subtasks`: Array of subtasks with status\n   - `UseCaseWithVersionAndTests` interface for typed use case data\n\n2. **Implement loadStoryWithFullContext()** function:\n   - Single comprehensive Prisma query with `include` clause\n   - Load all story fields including analysis fields (baAnalysis, architectAnalysis, designerAnalysis, contextExploration, uxDesigns)\n   - Include project, epic, useCaseLinks with versions, subtasks\n   - Return typed `StoryFullContext` object\n   - Throw descriptive error if story not found\n   - Add JSDoc documentation\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] `StoryFullContext` interface defined with all required fields\n- [ ] `loadStoryWithFullContext()` function implemented\n- [ ] Single Prisma query loads all data efficiently\n- [ ] Function returns typed result matching interface\n- [ ] Error handling for missing story\n- [ ] JSDoc comments explain usage\n- [ ] Unit tests verify correct data loading\n\n## Technical Notes\n\nFile: `backend/src/mcp/utils.ts`\n\nExample usage:\n```typescript\nconst context = await loadStoryWithFullContext(storyId);\n// context.story.description, context.useCases, etc.\n```	planning	7	\N	4	\N	\N	5269e325-16c7-4400-